          "severity": "low",
          "category": "test-coverage",
          "title": "Log-level demotion in autonomous.ts lacks a regression test",
          "body": "The PR adds a regression test in streaming.test.ts (lines 540-574) asserting that a malformed-JSON SSE frame triggers console.warn (not console.error), but the parallel changes in autonomous.ts at lines 122 and 230 have no equivalent regression test in autonomous.test.ts. Per .claude/rules/testing.md: 'Bug fixes require a regression test that reproduces the original failure.' Per .claude/rules/done.md: 'New behavior needs a test that fails without the change and passes with it.' Someone could revert either autonomous.ts catch block to console.error and no CI signal would fire. The asymmetry also weakens the commit's protective value: fd33a3f3 locks streaming.ts's log level via test, while 9fed1525 (autonomous.ts) does not. Fix: either add a similar plain-spy regression test to autonomous.test.ts covering both catch blocks, or document why autonomous is exempt (e.g. autonomous.test.ts is a different surface about to be migrated/deleted).",
          "confidence": "high"
        }
      ]
    },
